# Changelog standards

Use this rule when adding or editing changelog entries.

## Structure

- Keep a single `# Changelog` heading at the top.
- Wrap entries in `{% updates format="full" %}` and `{% endupdates %}`.
- Use one `{% update date="YYYY-MM-DD" tags="x.y.z" %}` block per release.
- Close every release block with `{% endupdate %}`.
- Add new releases at the top so entries remain reverse chronological.

## Entry format

- Start each release with an `##` title that summarizes the release.
- Group details under `#### Improvements` and `#### Fixes` when applicable.
- Use bullet points for scoped changes; keep each bullet specific and concise.
- Use present-perfect verbs for change bullets (for example: "Added", "Updated", "Fixed").

## Quality checks

- Ensure `tags` use semantic versioning and match the release being documented.
- Ensure the `date` is the actual release date in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.
- Keep tense and punctuation consistent across bullets.
- Remove trailing spaces and empty lines between blocks.
